title: JUI’s Candidate Ijaz Ahmed wins PK-74 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamiat Ulema Islam Pakistan (JUI-P)’ Candidate Ijaz Ahmed has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-74, Peshawar-III by securing 45,959 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Arbab Ullah Yar Khan who bagged 21,817 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 62.2 per cent.
